  "prompt": "What is the minimum level of mathematical proficiency required to graduate from West Point?",
  "response": "To graduate from the United States Military Academy at West Point, cadets are required to complete a rigorous core curriculum that includes mathematics. The minimum level of mathematical proficiency required typically involves completing the following math courses:\n\n1. **MA103: Mathematical Modeling and Introduction to Calculus** - This course covers pre-calculus topics and introduces calculus.\n2. **MA104: Differential Calculus** - This course focuses on differential calculus and its applications.\n3. **MA205: Integral Calculus and Introduction to Differential Equations** - This course covers integral calculus and introduces differential equations.\n\nAdditionally, cadets are required to take at least one more advanced math course, such as:\n- **MA206: Vector Calculus and Differential Equations**\n- **MA363: Statistics for Engineers and Scientists**\n- **MA364: Engineering Mathematics**\n\nThe exact courses may vary slightly depending on the academic year and specific program requirements, but the above courses represent the general mathematical proficiency expected of a West Point graduate. This level of proficiency ensures that graduates have a solid foundation in calculus, differential equations, and other advanced mathematical topics necessary for their future roles as military officers and leaders.",
